    "gp_section_607777335885693526": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "9954f1b632f57bdc643e7c0822accced77215b30845dc478c7669156d00e89b5_1_1_0_0__1",
        "ggEtTtuFzo8_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/Rectangle_41017.png",
        "ggEtTtuFzo8_srcSet_mobile_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/2nd_section.png",
        "ggI1A7sP_Yz_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/2nd_section.png",
        "ggwdZ1yHpLW_text": "<span style=\"color:#151515;\">Why Do We Really</span><span style=\"color:#E5C085;\"> Grind&nbsp;&amp; Clench?</span>",
        "ggy1c_a2wFu_text": "<p>Our view is that it's because the teeth don't fit together correctly. Sometimes this occurs due to malocclussion, but sometimes it is induced from orthodontics, extractions or bad dental work.</p>"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-607777335885693526"
    },
    "gp_section_607777432371462742": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "46541c837324997adcf9980eeab6c6421e853ef6f1b5c7e4895efe2794ae790a_1_1_0_0__1",
        "gg7FE_LxBx4_childItem_0": "<p><span style=\"color:#E5C085;\"><strong>Elevation and Depression:</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#4B5563;\">Elevation closes the mouth, while depression opens it.</span></p>",
        "gg7FE_LxBx4_childItem_1": "<p><span style=\"color:#E5C085;\"><strong>Protrusion and Retrusion:</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#4B5563;\">Elevation closes the mouth, while depression opens it.</span></p>",
        "gg7FE_LxBx4_childItem_2": "<p><span style=\"color:#E5C085;\"><strong>Lateral Excursion (Side-to-Side Movement):</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#4B5563;\">This allows the jaw to move left or right, essential for grinding food.</span></p>",
        "gg7FE_LxBx4_childItem_3": "<p><span style=\"color:#E5C085;\"><strong>Rotational and Translational Movements:</strong></span> <span style=\"color:#4B5563;\">These combined motions allow for complex movements such as chewing. The jaw rotates initially, then slides down the TMJ socket to open fully.</span></p>",
        "ggHmpKTmQqV_html5Url": "https://cdn.shopify.com/videos/c/o/v/2cd3deb506b54b009063f7270ab5cf2e.mp4",
        "ggHmpKTmQqV_poster_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/screencapture-reviv-substack-p-my-view-on-bruxism-teeth-grinding-2026-02-02-16_02_26_1.png",
        "ggHmpKTmQqV_vimeoUrl": "https://vimeo.com/1095883398",
        "ggHmpKTmQqV_youtubeUrl": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NfASaHFN1zg",
        "ggIe0iDtsg5_text": "<p>The jaw actually has a complex set of movements that can be easily disrupted, thereby causing bruxism:</p>",
        "ggfuQy3tXli_text": "<span style=\"color:#151515;\">The Engineering</span><span style=\"color:#E5C085;\"> of the Jaw</span>"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-607777432371462742"
    },
    "gp_section_607847350211183190": {
      "settings": {
        "checksum": "098270bc14db920b4ec2769cd2f3534402f5c95b2f646bbe900c78cb388c942e_1_1_0_0__1",
        "gg6GJbX6CM9_text": "<p>Waking up with a sore, stiff jaw is a clear sign of overnight clenching. This tension can last throughout the day and affect eating and speaking.</p>",
        "ggCzv6G9-eN_text": "<p>Enamel doesn't regenerate. Grinding wears it down permanently, exposing inner layers and causing sensitivity to hot, cold, and sweet foods.</p>",
        "ggLlzIenFpW_text": "<span style=\"color:#151515;\">Why </span><span style=\"color:#E5C185;\">Grinding &amp; Clenching</span><span style=\"color:#151515;\"> Shouldn't Be Ignored</span>",
        "ggMA-nF0TQw_text": "<p><span style=\"color:#E5C185;\">Poor Sleep Quality</span></p>",
        "ggYUaEkEtIM_alt": "Alt Image",
        "ggYUaEkEtIM_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/icon2.png",
        "ggYUaEkEtIM_title": "Image Title",
        "ggYeEheYm5x_text": "<p><span style=\"color:#E5C185;\">Tooth Damage &amp; Sensitivity</span></p>",
        "ggZ3DnGlD-__text": "<p><span style=\"color:#E5C185;\">Morning Jaw Tightness</span></p>",
        "ggaX5TeAaCU_text": "<p>Grinding disrupts your sleep architecture, preventing deep, restorative rest. Poor sleep increases stress, which worsens grinding—a vicious cycle.</p>",
        "gggvqLg6zjw_text": "<p><span style=\"color:#E5C185;\">Headaches &amp; Facial Fatigue</span></p>",
        "gggxF3LE-GR_alt": "Alt Image",
        "gggxF3LE-GR_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/icon3.png",
        "gggxF3LE-GR_title": "Image Title",
        "ggisrWoEtEI_alt": "Alt Image",
        "ggisrWoEtEI_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/icon1.png",
        "ggisrWoEtEI_title": "Image Title",
        "ggl71JLespp_text": "<p>Chronic jaw muscle tension often radiates to the temples and forehead, causing persistent tension headaches and facial discomfort.</p>",
        "ggq0iildLt2_alt": "Alt Image",
        "ggq0iildLt2_srcSet_desktop_src": "https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0706/4243/4289/files/icon4.png",
        "ggq0iildLt2_title": "Image Title"
      },
      "type": "gp-section-607847350211183190"
    },
